---
alwaysApply: true
---

project:
name: accomtz
description: >
React Native Expo app for Accomtz. Students browse and book properties.
Agents upload and manage their listings. Includes login, booking,
and agent management flows.

tech_stack:

- React Native
- Expo Router
- TypeScript
- Axios for API requests
- Zustand or Redux Toolkit for state management
- Expo Secure Store for tokens
  -jwt token for authentication and authorization
- Cloudinary for displaying media

conventions:

- Use TypeScript strict mode.
- Use functional components with hooks (no class components).
- Follow folder structure:
  app/ # screens (expo-router)
  components/ # UI components
  services/ # API calls
  constants/ # theme, colors
  store/ # global state (Zustand or Redux)
  types/ # shared TypeScript interfaces
- Use camelCase for variables, PascalCase for components.
- Separate UI from logic (custom hooks for business logic).
- Import from "@/..." aliases for clean paths.
- In any form input validate the user inputs always.

ai_rules:

- Always type props and states explicitly.
- For navigation, use `expo-router` conventions.
- Use React Native’s built-in components and @expo/vector-icons.
- When calling backend APIs, use Axios with a pre-configured baseURL.
- Use async storage through `expo-secure-store` for sensitive tokens.
- Follow component-driven design — smaller, reusable pieces.
- Keep UI consistent with app theme.
  -always maintain theming dark and light modes
- Use safe area and responsive styles (Dimensions API).

libraries:

- expo
- react-native
- expo-router
- axios
- expo-secure-store
- react-native-gesture-handler
- react-native-reanimated
- zustand (or redux-toolkit)
- @expo/vector-icons
